      <div class="row">
        <p class="descBody col s8 offset-s2">
          This is a polyalphabetic substitution cipher that that use characters of a sentence or word as keys.
          The characters are split into a multiple subkeys.
          The more letters are provided as keys, the stronger it will be the encrypted message. The key can be a combo
          of words and numbers just more make it more harder. A key of a sentence of 3 words is normally sufficient for a normal distribution.
          Mathematically the encryption can be denoted as C = (p, k) where j = 0.
        </p>
